-- Greek Politicians Strike an Agreement on Austerity Steps for Financial Aid
-- B y   E l e n i   C h r e p a   a n d   C h r i s t o s   Z i o t i s
-- 2012-02-09T14:55:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-09/greek-politicians-reach-agreement-on-austerity-steps-for-financial-bailout.html
Greece ’s government has reached a
deal on austerity measures required for a 130 billion-euro ($173
billion) financing package, according to an e-mailed statement
from the Greek Prime Minister’s press office.   “Discussions between the Greek government and the troika
were successfully completed this morning,” according to the
statement. “Political leaders have agreed with the result of
those negotiations. Therefore there is a general agreement in
the context of the new program ahead of tonight’s Eurogroup
meeting.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eleni Chrepa in Athens at 
